## GNOME Terminal

### Developer
The [GNOME Project](/The_GNOME_Project), a collective of [programmers](/Programmer) who apparently have too much time on their hands.

### Stable Release
As of January 3, 2025, the latest iteration is 3.56.2. One can only assume the intervening versions were minor tweaks, or perhaps elaborate jokes.

### Repository
The source code, for those who find solace in endless lines of text, resides at gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-terminal.git. It's a [repository](/Repository_(version_control)), a digital graveyard for code, if you will.

### Written In
[C](/C_(programming_language)). A language as practical and unadorned as a well-worn leather jacket.

### Operating System
Primarily [Linux](/Linux) and other [Unix-like](/Unix-like) systems. The places where actual work gets done, or so I'm told.

### Type
A [Terminal Emulator](/Terminal_Emulator). It pretends to be a [physical terminal](/Terminal_(computing)), a relic from a bygone era, but it lives within your shiny graphical [desktop environment](/Desktop_environment). How quaint.

### License
[GPL-3.0-or-later](/GNU_General_Public_License). Free to use, modify, and distribute. Because apparently, sharing is caring.

### Website
wiki.gnome.org/Apps/Terminal. A digital shrine for those who worship at the altar of functionality.

